<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,805,2026]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[228,318,805,831]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="25.[151,270,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[261,1324,208,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[244,1337,194,1936]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Habitus. 9. Hovorodon maxillosum (Drury, 1773), female; 10. Hovorodon santacruzensis (Hovore &amp; Santos-Silva, 2004), paratype male; 11. idem, paratype female; 12. Mallodon arabicum Buquet, 1843, male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276174/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[285,318,805,831]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Central area of head, between the antennal tubercles and middle of upper ocular lobes, with gibbosity slightly marked on each side of longitudinal dorsal furrow. Punctures of dorsal face distinctly coarser and deeper laterally and towards occiput. Antennal tubercles coarsely punctate at basal half and distinctly finer at apical half, mainly at apex. Length of clypeus approximately 
<number box="[1082,1133,917,943]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="0.35">0.35</number>
times width; frontal edge strongly emarginated; surface not strongly sloped in relation to the front. Distance between upper ocular lobes 
<number box="[151,188,992,1018]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="3.2">3.2</number>
times width of scape at apex; distance between lower ocular lobes 
<number box="[969,1005,992,1018]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="3.7">3.7</number>
times width of scape at apex. Ocular carina narrow and well marked from base of antennal tubercles to posterior upper ocular edge. Hypostomal area (
<figureCitation box="[221,313,1066,1092]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[227,1316,205,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[225,1318,194,1747]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35, head and prothorax, ventral view: 33. Hovorodon maxillosum, female; 34. H. santacruzensis, paratype male; 35. idem, paratype female. 36 – 52, mandibles: 36. Nothopleurus castaneus, male, dorsal view; 37. idem, female, dorsal view; 38. N. lobigenis, male, dorsal view; 39. idem, female, dorsal view; 40. N. subsulcatus, male, lateral view; 41. N. madericus, male, lateral view; 42. idem, female, dorsal view; 43. Hovorodon subcancellatum, male, dorsal view; 44. idem, male, lateral view; 45. idem, female, dorsal view; 46. H. bituberculatum, male, dorsal view; 47. idem, male, lateral view; 48. idem, female, dorsal view; 49. H. maxillosum, male, dorsal view; 50. idem, female, dorsal view; 51. H. santacruzensis, male, dorsal view; 52. idem, female, dorsal view. 53 – 56, metatarsus: 53. Mallodon downesii Hope, 1843, male, dorsal view; 54. idem, lateral view; 55. M. arabicum, male, dorsal view; 56. idem, male, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276178/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[280,313,1066,1092]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
) distinctly depressed centrally near mentum; surface coarsely vermiculate, wholly, finely punctate; setation long and sparse towards gula and shorter towards mentum. Hypostomal carina (
<figureCitation box="[1297,1383,1104,1130]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[227,1316,205,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[225,1318,194,1747]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35, head and prothorax, ventral view: 33. Hovorodon maxillosum, female; 34. H. santacruzensis, paratype male; 35. idem, paratype female. 36 – 52, mandibles: 36. Nothopleurus castaneus, male, dorsal view; 37. idem, female, dorsal view; 38. N. lobigenis, male, dorsal view; 39. idem, female, dorsal view; 40. N. subsulcatus, male, lateral view; 41. N. madericus, male, lateral view; 42. idem, female, dorsal view; 43. Hovorodon subcancellatum, male, dorsal view; 44. idem, male, lateral view; 45. idem, female, dorsal view; 46. H. bituberculatum, male, dorsal view; 47. idem, male, lateral view; 48. idem, female, dorsal view; 49. H. maxillosum, male, dorsal view; 50. idem, female, dorsal view; 51. H. santacruzensis, male, dorsal view; 52. idem, female, dorsal view. 53 – 56, metatarsus: 53. Mallodon downesii Hope, 1843, male, dorsal view; 54. idem, lateral view; 55. M. arabicum, male, dorsal view; 56. idem, male, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276178/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1352,1383,1104,1130]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
) not elevated. Maxillary palpomere III as long as IV. Apex of labial palps reaching base of maxillary palpomere IV. Galea surpassing the apex of maxillary palpomere I.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,805,2026]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[343,433,1216,1242]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="25.[151,270,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[261,1324,208,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[244,1337,194,1936]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Habitus. 9. Hovorodon maxillosum (Drury, 1773), female; 10. Hovorodon santacruzensis (Hovore &amp; Santos-Silva, 2004), paratype male; 11. idem, paratype female; 12. Mallodon arabicum Buquet, 1843, male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276174/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[403,433,1216,1242]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<number box="[636,673,1216,1242]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times longer than head (
<emphasis box="[990,1060,1216,1241]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">major</emphasis>
male); dorsal carina (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1427,1216,1242]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[227,1316,205,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[225,1318,194,1747]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35, head and prothorax, ventral view: 33. Hovorodon maxillosum, female; 34. H. santacruzensis, paratype male; 35. idem, paratype female. 36 – 52, mandibles: 36. Nothopleurus castaneus, male, dorsal view; 37. idem, female, dorsal view; 38. N. lobigenis, male, dorsal view; 39. idem, female, dorsal view; 40. N. subsulcatus, male, lateral view; 41. N. madericus, male, lateral view; 42. idem, female, dorsal view; 43. Hovorodon subcancellatum, male, dorsal view; 44. idem, male, lateral view; 45. idem, female, dorsal view; 46. H. bituberculatum, male, dorsal view; 47. idem, male, lateral view; 48. idem, female, dorsal view; 49. H. maxillosum, male, dorsal view; 50. idem, female, dorsal view; 51. H. santacruzensis, male, dorsal view; 52. idem, female, dorsal view. 53 – 56, metatarsus: 53. Mallodon downesii Hope, 1843, male, dorsal view; 54. idem, lateral view; 55. M. arabicum, male, dorsal view; 56. idem, male, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276178/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1397,1427,1216,1242]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
) narrow and strongly elevated, obliquely sloped near apex; outer face moderately densely punctate; inner face convex; inner lower margin projected as a plate at apical half, and with some teeth, more distinct at apical third of the plate. Scape surpassing posterior edge of eyes; somewhat coarsely punctate, mainly laterally and dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,805,2026]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Anterior angles of prothorax feebly projected forward; posterior angles variable, generally rounded. Elytra glabrous, finely punctate and somewhat finely rugose throughout. Width of metepisterna (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1369,1440,1466]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 64" captionStartId="33.[151,274,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[192,1387,197,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[177,1399,194,1925]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 64. Metepisternum, male. 57. Nothopleurus castaneus; 58. N. lobigenis; 59. N. subsulcatus; 60. N. madericus; 61. Hovorodon subcancellatum; 62. H. bituberculatum; 63. H. maxillosum; 64. H. santacruzensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276179/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1338,1369,1440,1466]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="64.0">64</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[1384,1435,1440,1466]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="0.25">0.25</number>
times of length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,805,2026]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Female (
<figureCitation box="[304,393,1514,1540]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="25.[151,270,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[261,1324,208,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[244,1337,194,1936]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Habitus. 9. Hovorodon maxillosum (Drury, 1773), female; 10. Hovorodon santacruzensis (Hovore &amp; Santos-Silva, 2004), paratype male; 11. idem, paratype female; 12. Mallodon arabicum Buquet, 1843, male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276174/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[362,393,1514,1540]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head, without mandibles, 
<number box="[738,775,1514,1540]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="0.7">0.7</number>
times length of prothorax. Sculpture of dorsal face of head, and area behind eyes as in male. Labrum occasionally longer in male (from 
<number box="[1151,1267,1552,1578]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3 to 0.4</number>
times width). Distance between upper ocular lobes 
<number box="[599,636,1589,1615]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="2.8">2.8</number>
times width of scape at apex; distance between lower ocular lobes 
<number box="[151,188,1626,1652]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="3.2">3.2</number>
times width of scape at apex. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[683,769,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[227,1316,205,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[225,1318,194,1747]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35, head and prothorax, ventral view: 33. Hovorodon maxillosum, female; 34. H. santacruzensis, paratype male; 35. idem, paratype female. 36 – 52, mandibles: 36. Nothopleurus castaneus, male, dorsal view; 37. idem, female, dorsal view; 38. N. lobigenis, male, dorsal view; 39. idem, female, dorsal view; 40. N. subsulcatus, male, lateral view; 41. N. madericus, male, lateral view; 42. idem, female, dorsal view; 43. Hovorodon subcancellatum, male, dorsal view; 44. idem, male, lateral view; 45. idem, female, dorsal view; 46. H. bituberculatum, male, dorsal view; 47. idem, male, lateral view; 48. idem, female, dorsal view; 49. H. maxillosum, male, dorsal view; 50. idem, female, dorsal view; 51. H. santacruzensis, male, dorsal view; 52. idem, female, dorsal view. 53 – 56, metatarsus: 53. Mallodon downesii Hope, 1843, male, dorsal view; 54. idem, lateral view; 55. M. arabicum, male, dorsal view; 56. idem, male, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276178/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[738,769,1626,1652]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
) almost glabrous on outer face. Antennae attaining basal one-third of elytra; scape not surpassing posterior edge of eyes. Hypostomal area (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1203,1664,1690]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[227,1316,205,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[225,1318,194,1747]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 56. 33 – 35, head and prothorax, ventral view: 33. Hovorodon maxillosum, female; 34. H. santacruzensis, paratype male; 35. idem, paratype female. 36 – 52, mandibles: 36. Nothopleurus castaneus, male, dorsal view; 37. idem, female, dorsal view; 38. N. lobigenis, male, dorsal view; 39. idem, female, dorsal view; 40. N. subsulcatus, male, lateral view; 41. N. madericus, male, lateral view; 42. idem, female, dorsal view; 43. Hovorodon subcancellatum, male, dorsal view; 44. idem, male, lateral view; 45. idem, female, dorsal view; 46. H. bituberculatum, male, dorsal view; 47. idem, male, lateral view; 48. idem, female, dorsal view; 49. H. maxillosum, male, dorsal view; 50. idem, female, dorsal view; 51. H. santacruzensis, male, dorsal view; 52. idem, female, dorsal view. 53 – 56, metatarsus: 53. Mallodon downesii Hope, 1843, male, dorsal view; 54. idem, lateral view; 55. M. arabicum, male, dorsal view; 56. idem, male, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276178/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1173,1203,1664,1690]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
) without transverse furrow near anterior edge. Width of metepisterna 
<number box="[732,769,1701,1727]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="0.3">0.3</number>
times length.
</paragraph>
